{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Planetary systems outside our own"},{"time":2000,"text":"are like distant cities whose lights we can see twinkling,"},{"time":5000,"text":"but whose streets we can't walk."},{"time":8000,"text":"By studying those twinkling lights though,"},{"time":10000,"text":"we can learn about how stars and planets interact"},{"time":13000,"text":"to form their own ecosystem"},{"time":15000,"text":"and make habitats that are amenable to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"In this image of the Tokyo skyline,"},{"time":20000,"text":"I've hidden data"},{"time":22000,"text":"from the newest planet-hunting space telescope on the block,"},{"time":24000,"text":"the Kepler Mission."},{"time":26000,"text":"Can you see it?"},{"time":28000,"text":"There we go."},{"time":30000,"text":"This is just a tiny part of the sky the Kepler stares at,"},{"time":33000,"text":"where it searches for planets"},{"time":35000,"text":"by measuring the light from over 150,000 stars,"},{"time":38000,"text":"all at once, every half hour,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and very precisely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"And what we're looking for"},{"time":44000,"text":"is the tiny dimming of light"},{"time":46000,"text":"that is caused by a planet passing in front of one of these stars"},{"time":49000,"text":"and blocking some of that starlight from getting to us."},{"time":52000,"text":"In just over two years of operations,"},{"time":55000,"text":"we've found over 1,200"},{"time":57000,"text":"potential new planetary systems around other stars."},{"time":60000,"text":"To give you some perspective,"},{"time":62000,"text":"in the previous two decades of searching,"},{"time":65000,"text":"we had only known about 400"},{"time":67000,"text":"prior to Kepler."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"When we see these little dips in the light,"},{"time":71000,"text":"we can determine a number of things."},{"time":73000,"text":"For one thing, we can determine that there's a planet there,"},{"time":75000,"text":"but also how big that planet is"},{"time":78000,"text":"and how far it is away from its parent star."},{"time":81000,"text":"That distance is really important"},{"time":83000,"text":"because it tells us"},{"time":85000,"text":"how much light the planet receives overall."},{"time":87000,"text":"And that distance and knowing that amount of light is important"},{"time":90000,"text":"because it's a little like you or I sitting around a campfire:"},{"time":93000,"text":"You want to be close enough to the campfire so that you're warm,"},{"time":95000,"text":"but not so close"},{"time":97000,"text":"that you're too toasty and you get burned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"However, there's more to know about your parent star"},{"time":102000,"text":"than just how much light you receive overall."},{"time":104000,"text":"And I'll tell you why."},{"time":106000,"text":"This is our star. This is our Sun."},{"time":109000,"text":"It's shown here in visible light."},{"time":111000,"text":"That's the light that you can see with your own human eyes."},{"time":113000,"text":"You'll notice that it looks pretty much"},{"time":115000,"text":"like the iconic yellow ball --"},{"time":117000,"text":"that Sun that we all draw when we're children."},{"time":119000,"text":"But you'll notice something else,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and that's that the face of the Sun"},{"time":123000,"text":"has freckles."},{"time":125000,"text":"These freckles are called sunspots,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and they are just one of the manifestations"},{"time":129000,"text":"of the Sun's magnetic field."},{"time":131000,"text":"They also cause the light from the star to vary."},{"time":134000,"text":"And we can measure this"},{"time":136000,"text":"very, very precisely with Kepler and trace their effects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"However, these are just the tip of the iceberg."},{"time":142000,"text":"If we had UV eyes or X-ray eyes,"},{"time":145000,"text":"we would really see"},{"time":147000,"text":"the dynamic and dramatic effects"},{"time":149000,"text":"of our Sun's magnetic activity --"},{"time":151000,"text":"the kind of thing that happens on other stars as well."},{"time":154000,"text":"Just think, even when it's cloudy outside,"},{"time":156000,"text":"these kind of events are happening"},{"time":158000,"text":"in the sky above you all the time."},{"time":162000,"text":"So when we want to learn whether a planet is habitable,"},{"time":165000,"text":"whether it might be amenable to life,"},{"time":167000,"text":"we want to know not only how much total light it receives"},{"time":169000,"text":"and how warm it is,"},{"time":171000,"text":"but we want to know about its space weather --"},{"time":174000,"text":"this high-energy radiation,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the UV and the X-rays"},{"time":178000,"text":"that are created by its star"},{"time":180000,"text":"and that bathe it in this bath of high-energy radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"And so, we can't really look"},{"time":185000,"text":"at planets around other stars"},{"time":187000,"text":"in the same kind of detail"},{"time":189000,"text":"that we can look at planets in our own solar system."},{"time":192000,"text":"I'm showing here Venus, Earth and Mars --"},{"time":194000,"text":"three planets in our own solar system that are roughly the same size,"},{"time":197000,"text":"but only one of which"},{"time":199000,"text":"is really a good place to live."},{"time":201000,"text":"But what we can do in the meantime"},{"time":203000,"text":"is measure the light from our stars"},{"time":206000,"text":"and learn about this relationship"},{"time":208000,"text":"between the planets and their parent stars"},{"time":210000,"text":"to suss out clues"},{"time":212000,"text":"about which planets might be good places"},{"time":214000,"text":"to look for life in the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Kepler won't find a planet"},{"time":218000,"text":"around every single star it looks at."},{"time":220000,"text":"But really, every measurement it makes"},{"time":222000,"text":"is precious,"},{"time":224000,"text":"because it's teaching us about the relationship"},{"time":226000,"text":"between stars and planets,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and how it's really the starlight"},{"time":230000,"text":"that sets the stage"},{"time":232000,"text":"for the formation of life in the universe."},{"time":234000,"text":"While it's Kepler the telescope, the instrument that stares,"},{"time":237000,"text":"it's we, life, who are searching."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}